# skills/.npmignore — exclusions applied to the skills/ subtree before
# pack. Only the stamped SKILL.md (produced by scripts/stamp-skill.mjs
# during prepack) ships in the tarball — the source template is a build
# input, not a publishable artifact.
#
# Why this lives here (and not at the package root): npm's pruning
# semantics for `.npmignore` apply most reliably to the directory the
# file lives in. A root `.npmignore` is sometimes shadowed by
# `package.json#files`. Co-locating the exclusion with the directory it
# governs sidesteps that ambiguity.
#
# DST-05 contract: verify-pack.mjs's FORBIDDEN_PATTERNS keeps /\.tmpl$/
# as a defense-in-depth check that fails the release if anything
# bypasses this exclusion.
**/*.tmpl
